Create custom project templates in Xcode


This path leads to the Mac OS project templates:
/Applications/Xcode.app/Contents/Developer/Library/Xcode/Templates/Project Templates/Mac

This one to the iOS project templates:
/Applications/Xcode.app/Contents/Developer/Platforms/iPhoneOS.platform/Developer/Library/Xcode/Templates/Project Templates/iOS


[In .xctemplate/TemplateInfo.plist]

### Identifier ###
  Every template has an identifier key which consist of a prefix and the name of the template.
  Apple uses a com.apple.dt.unit prefix, so every template provided by them has it.

### Kind ###
  Xcode Template Kind. Project or File.

### Ancestors ###
  Import settings from another Project Template.
  The Ancestore key defines the parents of the current template.

### Definitions ###
  Work with workplace. Can write to file example source code.

### Nodes ###
  Create or Copy Files to Project or File.

### Options ###
  New Project Wizard >> Choose Options for Project. Add Text Fields, Combo Boxes.

### Project ###
  Set Project Build Settings.

### Targets ###
  Set Build Settings, Build Phases for Targets.
  Link Libraries.

[Finder]
1. Go to ~/Library/Developer/Xcode
2. If the Templates directory does not exist, create it.
3. In the Templates directory, create another folder, called Custom.
4. Go to the default iOS project templates and copy the Single View Application.xctemplate.
5. Go back to the ~/Library/Developer/Xcode/Templates/Custom directory and paste it there.
6. Open .plist file of our template
7. change the identifier prefix with, let's say,  com.cshan.dt.unit.singleViewApplication

* Open Xcode and in the new project panel, you should be able to see your custom category with the project template in it.

### Customizations & Setup ###



